			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23440"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 9:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are only good pullable (without adds) gargs on the wall and on the gravestones just inside the gate. If you happen to get a banshee, charm it and send it to its death on your angry mob of mobs (hehe). A good way to minimize hits you take would be to Invis up (not many gargs see invis) and run to the corner straight left as you come through gate (running between the gravestones and the wall). Then break invis and run out, making sure they aggro on you on the way out. I only know of one trap outside the walls, and thats the spider trap between gargs and zone two. Best way to avoid this place is either to memorize where it is or run high up on the wall. That just about does it on gargs...... next week: soloing nightmares!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Impresario Amedaius Bladewhisper, 65 ladies' broken hearts and 141 aa meetings. <The Black Sheep of tunares flock she doesn't want to discuss>

