			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23441"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 9:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I see you found the spider traps.  The only advice I have for those is to try and stay as high up on the wall after you go past the guardians.  Once you are past the sharp point and near the boulders where the bats spawn, you should be ok.  
<br />

<br />
As far as pulling the gargoyles themselves, start off by only working the ones on top of the walls until you get a feel for how they aggro.  Some will come right off but others need a litlle coaxing.  You can also pull some of the gargs sitting on the gravestones by prox aggro, but be careful pulling these since some are linked to banshees.  If you mess up, the stone to port out is only a short dash away.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
