			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23587"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 3:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First, you definitely need the 64 charm for anything in the gargs area.
<br />

<br />
Second, I recommend leaving gargs &amp; doing hobs/wraiths - gargs are harder, give less exp &amp; have crappy loot.  Alternately the mephits aren't bad - exp not great but loot even better.
<br />

<br />
Third, generally the gargs camp includes all the gargs on the walls, the 2 or 3 just inside in the graveyard, all the bats outside, and a few of the giant spiders - they're uncharmable but add good dps to the swarm, and drop good loot.
<br />

<br />
The spider traps are a bit further back from the castle, and I think there's another deeper into the spider territory.  If you swarm right in front of the castle in the clearing you won't set them off.  If you do, just charm them &amp; suicide them - they don't have much hp.
<br />

<br />
The liches were always a pain for me - without Bellow the gargs take a while to pull - probably a dot is the best method, though that can be a bit too much aggro for a swarm.  Proximity pulling tends to aggro liches.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
