			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23836"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 12:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The giant spiders do NOT summon, but I think some or all of the little spiders that pop out of the traps do.  Also the named spiders summon.
<br />

<br />
The above posters are correct about the hobs, only the Scourge summon, the ones named &quot;Hobgoblin&quot; do not.  I pull all of them as well, proximity works for the first, and chain aggro picks up the rest.  MR is somewhat important since occasionally the scourges will try to root you.  Highsun pops them back to their spawn point, and if you're on the plateau, that's far enough away that they will not come back.
<br />

<br />
The &quot;wraith&quot; does summon, he's a static single spawn near a big rock in the center of the forest.  &quot;Nettling wraiths&quot; do NOT summon.  Avoid the liches in the forest though, they DO summon.
<br />

<br />
Normally when I do hobs, I do hobs and nettling wraiths, switching off between the two to allow the other to respawn.  I pull all the wraiths I can find (usually around 12 to 15), mostly along the shore of the river, and then grab a giant spider (there's one who sits alone), and pull them all back to the plateau.
<br />

<br />
Mephits - 3 methods to get to them, one is charm lich, sic on horse, break charm, get summoned, run away &amp; fade.  The second is to run through the cave using Kazumi's as needed, then fade at the top.  However, since you've got to be 64 to charm them, you should have fade by now anyway.  After RS 3 Fade was the first thing I bought.  If you don't have it yet...get it, it's by far your most useful tool post 63.  The third method is to camp a cleric up there, suicide, /corpse yourself up, and rez.  However, this may be considered an exploit.
<br />

<br />
Doing the mephits is really tricky because of all the wizard (lures, snare, root) and chanter (tash) casters.  I usually swap out Highsun for Veeshan when doing them, and you need to keep it up almost always.  VotS/epic helps too.  
<br />

<br />
I usually do them from the plateau, though you can also do them inside that big chamber, it's a bit tougher there.  You have to do smaller swarms because of all the casters, no more than about 6 or 8, more if there are fewer casters.  If I remember correctly (it's been a while) the casters are uncharmable, so you need to sic pets on them.
<br />

<br />
Incidentally...I've spent WAY too much time in PoN...if anyone knows some nice 55-57 mobs elsewhere that are swarmable please let me know<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  LCY/RCY in PoD works, but that's usually permacamped, or at least used to be, and you need both camps to not get bored.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
