			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23842"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 12:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
Bluze: You said &quot;pulling the gargoyles&quot;... I thought if you actually pulled with a song that if you screw up your swarm? (ie- the mobs not staying on your pet and gettin on you!) 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I primarily used proximity aggro to pull by throwing a chant on the first pet to be near the gate and running it up and down the side walls.  For those few that refuse to come down, you can either pop Kazumi's and stand directly beneath them, use boastful bellow which doens't carry much aggro, or like Amedaius mentions, use a low aggro song.  If you try and pull the straglers with a chant it will be a messy swarm until you can make it your next pet.  I don't do the gargoyles much anymore, there are easier targets in PoN for comparable loot and exp.
<br />

<br />
For the hobgoblins, you can get 9 or 10 on a single pull without the casters if you are careful.  There will still be 3 or 4 non casting hobgoblins left which can be pulled in a second stage.  Check out the hunting section for PoN, I have a short write up on how I do it.</span></td>
