				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="23934"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 7:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I trained several times to the Hedge zone out while learning how to avoid the summoning mobs around the hobgoblins.
<br />

<br />
I pull all the hobgobs EXCEPT the scourge hobs, with proximity aggro.  It isnt' that hard, took me 2-3 tries to figure it out.
<br />

<br />
Nettling wraiths are good, I grab them all and kite them also.  But my biggest tip for folks is to get a nightmare into each swarm from the plateau.  Just sick a pet up there, when your pet takes damage, break charm and they'll warp down.  Horsie can't be charmed, but gives 5% aa per, and if you just throw your pet at him every time, he'll die before your swarm does.
<br />

<br />
I also usually use a nettling wraith or 2 to kill all my hobs.  I swarm them around, get them all down to low HP and then have a backstabber (nettling wraiths are faster and backstab) finish them off one by one.  WAY faster than chant kiting.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy.</span></td>
