				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="24028"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 9:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you are dead set on doing the gargs, swarming is not your best option. The gargs do more dps, than hobbys or mephits, so the best thing to do is just a good ole fashion charmed pet battle with a spider. There are 2 spiders by the tree if looking at the front of castle area they will be to your right. Basically you want to hold aggro on spiders while the garg just kicks their a$.
<br />

<br />
Pull both spiders, chant to 80 percent each, grab a garg, have the garg chase the spiders while you chant, as soon as they turn on the garg, break charm, clearing aggro on pet, and recharm and do it again, You should get about 30% dammage per charm and the spiders give 5%aaxp per kill. 
<br />

<br />
Or you can do the same thing cept slow the spiders and have the garg kill them. 3gargs per 2slowed spiders is the ratio and that is about 15-18 percent aaxp. 
<br />

<br />
The traps you were refering too are right by the rocks straight out from the entrance and along the wall TT's lair is on. Those spiders dont summon either.
<br />

<br />
Summoning mobs, All banshees, misery mephits, nameds,agony mephits, Aligator thingys on shore, scourage hobbys. That is what summons around that side of the zone.
<br />

<br />
Someone else in this thread had it right, normal hobbys are best for swarming in that zone. I personally like mephits cause of the loot the blood sells very well.
<br />

<br />
Hobbys and Mephits can both be AoEd too.
<br />

<br />
Ialaran
<br />
Bristlebane</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
