				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="24316"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 3:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If I get any summoning mobs, I use one of a few different tricks:
<br />

<br />
Scourges - highsun.  They're too high to charm.  Incidentally, I think that pulling ALL the hobs then highsunning the scourges probably takes less time and effort than trying to pull just the non-summoning mobs.  In addition, it'd be nearly impossible to get all because there are at least 2 or 3 hobs right next to the scourges, and they aggro each other onto you.
<br />

<br />
Liches, Wraith, Gator - If only 1 or 2 I suicide them against the swarm.  If &gt;that I may just fade &amp; repull.  If you're careful you can avoid getting any.
<br />

<br />
When doing nettling wraiths, there are 2 spiders right next to the bank, then there's one solo one slightly inland from them.  That's the one I pull.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
