				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming Gargs! Veterans please give me some advice!<a name="24455"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 28 04 2:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hehe, I posted this elsewhere, but a fun trick you can try to get your scrawny bardic butt up onto the plateau is to charm a SUMMONING creature (i.e. a banshee) and sick it on a nightmare. Break charm after it gets down to half of its hps, and then (make sure selos is up at this point) once you get summoned put on some speed and then fade. This will get you your very own spot on that plateau where you can kill all the nightmares you want (they respawn slow though, i think 20-30 min). Also if you are feeling adventurous you can pull from the tunnels onto that nice flat open expanse. Just be careful if the Shade is up.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
